name: Garden of Eden
description:
In Abrahamic religions, the Garden of Eden (Hebrew: גַּן־עֵדֶן‎ – gan-ʿḖḏen) or Garden of God , also called the Terrestrial Paradise, is the biblical paradise described in Genesis books and Ezekiel.

The location of Eden is described at the head of the Persian Gulf, in southern Mesopotamia (now Iraq) where the Tigris and Euphrates rivers run into the sea and in Armenia.

its from a generative art project coded via Python - Pillow
Graphed via Pytorch implementation of various GANs , using the Turtle module
